726773f-c.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 68th Street
726773f-c.text:
Grand Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 68th Street (left
extending north), showing in fouu views at the corner,the
home of Judge William Burcham in 1872 which was demolished
in Jure 1925. It is said that this house is on the site of
the John Firth house of 1850. One Dovle was an occupant of
the house seen in these views. View No. four shows a rear
of the house viewed across the B.R.T. tracks parallelking
Borden Avenue.
February 1924
Views 1 and 4
Views 2S:3 1922
Euene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE RPPRODUCED.
